Barrier feefs are separated from the land by a lagoon. They 
are intricate ecosystems that are either ancient, modern, or 
somewhere inbetween. Shells form the reefs. The mounds of 
shells can sometimes reach hundreds of meters. Many animals 
thrive successfully in these reefs. 
I found this very interesting that a whole ecosystem can 
exist in just one reef. Also, it's made up of so many 
